      <h3>Credit Consumption Rates</h3>
      <p>HeyGen uses a single credit pool for all AI features. Credit consumption varies by feature:</p>
      <div class="table-scroll">
      <table>
        <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Credits per Minute</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Avatar III video generation</td><td>3/min</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Avatar IV / V video generation</td><td>20/min</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Video Agent (prompt-based)</td><td>20/min</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Audio Dubbing only (no lip sync)</td><td>2/min</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Full Video Translation (with lip sync)</td><td>5/min</td></tr>
      </table>
      </div>
      <p>This means a 3-minute video using Avatar V (the most lifelike engine) costs 60 credits on Pro — consuming 6% of the monthly 1,000-credit pool for a single short video. The same video using Avatar III costs only 9 credits. Real-world credit consumption depends heavily on which avatar engine and features are used.</p>

      <h3>Pricing Analysis</h3>
      <p>At $29/month (Creator), HeyGen offers good value for solo creators: 600 credits, 1080p export, voice cloning, and 175+ language support. The Pro tier at $49/month adds 4K export, faster processing, and edit/proofread translation scripts. The Business plan at $149/month + $20/seat is where team collaboration, SCORM export, LMS integrations, and interactive video features become available — making it the practical minimum for teams. Compared to Synthesia at $29/month (similar avatar capabilities) or Runway at $15/month (more creative-focused), HeyGen's broader feature set — especially video translation, product placement, and third-party model integration (Sora, Veo, Kling) — justifies the price premium for business users who need more than just avatar videos.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="design">
      <h2>Platform &amp; Build Quality</h2>
      <p>HeyGen is a browser-based SaaS platform accessible through any modern web browser. The AI Studio text-based editor, avatar generator, video translator, and Video Agent are all accessed through a unified web interface. The platform also offers a pay-as-you-go API for custom integrations.</p>

      <h3>Technology Architecture</h3>
      <p>HeyGen's core technology stack includes proprietary AI avatar rendering engines (Avatar III, IV, and the latest Avatar V), voice cloning and speech synthesis, and neural lip-sync for multilingual video translation. When a user creates a video, the system: (1) processes the script through a language model for natural phrasing and pacing; (2) generates or selects the appropriate avatar with matched facial expressions and gestures; (3) synchronizes lip movements to the speech audio using a neural lip-sync model; (4) applies any visual effects, backgrounds, or overlays; (5) renders the final video at the chosen resolution (up to 4K). The platform integrates third-party AI models — Sora, Veo, and Kling for video B-roll generation, Flux for image generation, and ElevenLabs for enhanced speech synthesis — through a unified interface.</p>

      <h3>Avatar Technology</h3>
      <p>HeyGen supports three avatar creation methods. Photo Avatar: upload a single static portrait photo, and the AI animates it into a talking video with natural facial expressions, lip-sync, and hand gestures. Public Avatar: a library of 500+ (Free) to 700+ (paid) pre-made stock avatars representing diverse demographics, styles, and professional settings. Digital Twin: film a short video of yourself (a few minutes of footage), and HeyGen creates a realistic digital clone that looks, moves, and sounds like you — enabling content creation at scale without repeated studio recordings. The latest Avatar V engine is described as the "most lifelike avatar ever made" by the company.</p>

      <h3>Security &amp; Compliance</h3>
      <p>HeyGen maintains GDPR compliance, SOC 2 Type II certification, CCPA compliance, and compliance with the EU AI Act and Data Privacy Framework. Enterprise plans include SAML/SSO, SCIM user provisioning, team member MFA enforcement, audit logs, and password-protected video URLs. The platform's security certifications are clearly displayed on the website and represent a meaningful compliance investment.</p>
    </section>

